This is confusing as there may have been like 5 guests, not exactly an overwhelmingly busy night.  after getting home and being disappointed with my meal, I immediately reached out to your restaurant and after multiple rings, I was routed to a call center, I explained my situation and was assured that the general manager would reach out to me within 48 hours to remedy the situation. a week later I called back and got the same information  If I was dining in I would have been able to resolve this issue immediately, but this situation has gone on for way longer than I should have had to endure  Finally was reached out to by the GM and told that I would receive some Discount vouchers from corporate instead of offering to refund me. I replied and have not heard back for days. I will be reaching out to corporate and see if they can take a close look at this location based on other's recent experience's I think things need to be addressed here. I do not plan on returning to this location anytime soon.

The food was awful. I mean, really, really bad. First off we were in a time crunch. From the moment we walked in, we only had an hour and ten minutes to eat. I say only because we ended up cutting it close. Normally that would have been plenty of time at a chain restaurant. Not this time. We started off with two Cokes. Ever have straight Coke syrup? Well, now I have. It wasn't actually pure syrup, it had flat water in it too. So we had flat, sickly sweet Coke.  Delicious. I ordered their Cajun pasta, she ordered a cheeseburger. Then we waited. And waited. And waited. All of a sudden, we went from having an hour, to having 30 minutes. After waiting half an hour, in a TGI Fridays that had maybe a half dozen other people in it, the food came. Cajun pasta. Looked tasty. Its fettuccini in a creamy sauce, with res peppers, a little spicy, with chicken, and shrimp. It should be pink. It was not pink. It was brown. It looked like beef stroganoff served at a homeless shelter. The chicken was rubbery.  The dish tasted burnt. The chicken, the shrimp, the peppers, the sauce, even the pasta itself, they all had the flavor of char. How the he'll can you make pasta taste like an ashtray? The breadstick it comes with was not burned however. Probably because it came out five minute minutes after the food. I'm guessing it was the second one they cooked.  The first is probably being used to draw a picture. Her cheeseburger, ordered medium well, was well burned. Blackened. Chared. It was tough, and looked like charcoal. Her fries tasted like they were cooked hours before and reheated. It was disgusting overall. I usually don't mind these places. TGI Fridays, Ruby Tuesdays etc. Ill be avoiding this one from now on though.
